---
import { Image } from 'astro:assets';
import ShanaPhoto from '../assets/shana-about.jpg';
import Layout from '../layouts/BlogPost.astro';
---

<Layout
	title="About Shana | Hosting Decoded"
	description="Shana is a Long Beach, CA Airbnb Superhost and Guest Favorite with 3 years of hosting experience. Hosting Decoded is her resource hub for short-term rental hosts who want better systems, stronger reviews, and more revenue."
	pubDate={new Date('April 13 2026')}
>

	<Image
		src={ShanaPhoto}
		alt="Shana, founder of Hosting Decoded"
		width={500}
		height={228}
		class="about-photo"
	/>

	<p>
		Hi, I'm Shana, a Long Beach, California-based Airbnb Superhost, Guest Favorite,
		and the person behind Hosting Decoded.
	</p>

	<p>
		I've been hosting for about three years, operating a 2-unit rental property in Long Beach.
		Like most hosts, I didn't start with a system. I started with a spare unit, a lot of
		enthusiasm, and a steep learning curve. Pricing, guest communication, turnovers,
		maintenance, reviews. I figured it all out the hard way.
	</p>

	<p>
		After a while, I noticed a pattern: most of the friction in hosting came from the same
		few things. Guests arriving without knowing where anything was. Repeat questions about
		check-out, the WiFi, the parking. Small confusions that added up to extra messages, extra
		stress, and reviews that could have been five stars but weren't.
	</p>

	<p>
		The fix I kept coming back to was a proper welcome guidebook, not a Google Doc with a
		bullet list, but a real, polished guide that helped guests settle in quickly, answered
		their questions before they asked, and made every stay feel intentional. A guide that
		worked so well I didn't have to repeat the same information over and over.
	</p>

	<p>
		I looked for a template that matched the level of care I was trying to put into my
		property. I couldn't find one. Everything out there was either generic, poorly designed, or
		obviously made by someone who had never actually hosted. So I designed my own.
	</p>

	<p>
		<a href="https://shanadesigns.gumroad.com/l/airbnb-guidebook-template">The Complete Airbnb Guidebook</a> is now
		available for any host who wants a faster path to a smoother operation. It's
		designer-crafted, fully editable in Canva, and takes under an hour to make your own.
		Built from real hosting experience, not a design brief.
	</p>

	<h2>What Hosting Decoded Is</h2>

	<p>
		Hosting Decoded exists to help hosts improve their operations, guest experience, and
		revenue through practical, actionable systems and resources. The kind that actually
		get used, not just bookmarked.
	</p>

	<p>I write about three things:</p>

	<ul>
		<li><strong>Guest Experience:</strong> creating stays that earn 5-star reviews and bring guests back</li>
		<li><strong>Hosting 101:</strong> the fundamentals every host needs to get right from day one</li>
		<li><strong>Earnings:</strong> pricing strategy, revenue optimization, and scaling your operation</li>
	</ul>

	<p>
		If you're just getting started or trying to sharpen what you've already built,
		you're in the right place.
	</p>

	<h2>Find Me</h2>

	<ul>
		<li>TikTok: <a href="https://www.tiktok.com/@hosting.decoded" target="_blank">@hosting.decoded</a>, hosting tips and behind-the-scenes</li>
		<li>Instagram: <a href="https://www.instagram.com/11thandNew" target="_blank">@11thandNew</a>, my Long Beach properties</li>
		<li>The guidebook: <a href="https://shanadesigns.gumroad.com/l/airbnb-guidebook-template">shanadesigns.gumroad.com</a></li>
	</ul>

</Layout>

<style>
	.about-photo {
		width: 100%;
		max-width: 500px;
		height: auto;
		border-radius: 8px;
		display: block;
		margin-bottom: 2rem;
	}
</style>
